## Known Issues

* fix Dump bug which reproduced a configkey for each field in the struct instead of a single key for the entire struct and nested keys for the fields:

```json
{
 "tls": {
    "enabled": false,
    "cert_file": "server.crt",
    "key_file": "server.key",
    "port": 8443
  },
  "tls.cert_file": "server.crt",
  "tls.enabled": false,
  "tls.key_file": "server.key",
  "tls.port": 8443
}
```

* make at least Getter/Setter and Dumping thread-safe f.e. using a RWMutex -> be aware that "read" access like GetFieldValue and GetConfigKey might need to acquire write locks f.e. when fields are initialized on read access

* fix GetFieldValue/GetConfigValue to initialize nil pointers to structs on read access otherwise f.e.:
GetFieldValue("tls") returns nil when not initialized but GetFieldValue("tls.enabled") returns false and a subsequent GetFieldValue("tls") returns the initialized struct.
Always initializing is the preferred approach so we don't need to check for nil (at least for structs).
Alternative: disallow access to structs and only allow access to members, the struct can still be accessed and modified through Config[T].Data field.